Phoenix Beverages of Mauritius Third-Quarter Profit Drops 41%; Sales Gain

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-11T06:31:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/phoenix-beverages-of-mauritius-third-quarter-profit-drops-41-sales-gain.html
Phoenix Beverages Ltd. (PBL) , the largest
beverages company in Mauritius by market value, said fiscal
third-quarter net income fell to 38.5 million Mauritian rupees
from 64.8 million rupees a year earlier.  Revenue in the three months through March increased to
888.7 million rupees from 783.4 million a year earlier, the Port
Louis-based company said in a statement posted on the website of
the Stock Exchange of Mauritius today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  